<br>The answer is simple. There is no definite list of mandatory courses for health and social care professionals.<br><br>For a training course to be considered mandatory, it must meet one or more of the following criteria:<br>
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-36_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-37_">For example, there is a statutory requirement under the Health and Safety at Work Act 1974.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-39_">Training is required for all employees throughout the organisation.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-41_">It is a requirement of the CQC or the local authority.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-45_">What is mandatory training for social care?</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-mandatory-training-for-social-care--the-mandatory-traininng-group-uk--1679190515457.jpg?v=1679190515" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-mandatory-training-for-social-care--the-mandatory-traininng-group-uk--1679190515457.jpg?v=1679190515 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-mandatory-training-for-social-care--the-mandatory-traininng-group-uk--1679190515457_500x.jpg?v=1679190515 320w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="What is mandatory training for social care - The Mandatory Traininng Group UK -" title="What is mandatory training for social care - The Mandatory Traininng Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-46_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-47_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-49_">Care managers must provide mandatory training for their employees following statutory requirements, such as the Health and Safety at Work Act, those of the local authority, and those specified by the CQC.<br>
